cff-version: 1.2.0
message: "If you use this software, please cite it as below and the papers it implements."
title: "FlagGAM: rule-basis generalized additive models (from-scratch implementation)"
version: "0.1.0"
license: Apache-2.0
repository-code: "https://github.com/danielwlazlo/flag-gam"
abstract: >
  A from-scratch Python implementation of FlagGAM (Zhao & Welsch, 2026) and the
  Univariate Flagging Algorithm (Sheth et al., 2019).  The package provides
  sklearn-compatible classifiers and regressors that build interpretable rule-basis
  generalized additive models from tabular data.

references:
  - type: article
    title: "FlagGAM: Rule-Basis Generalized Additive Models"
